I actually take a different approach. Good moods are fickle, motivation is difficult. Instead, I think you need diligence and discipline to make it through doing art. And honestly, you might be on the right track with exercise. Exercise is great for depression, funny enough, and for training the discipline muscle.

But don’t wait too long to begin some drawing practice if it’s something you really want, as it’s at minimum a time-spent skill. Get a small sketchbook, a pencil, and keep it somewhere easily accessible. After your exercise, do an art exercise, even if it’s just line practice. That now is your art reps. Mainly, you want to lower the investment needed to start drawing at any period of the day. If you can make it easy to start and stop, you can train yourself to do it more and feel less strongly about it. Good luck anon, I hope things improve for you.
